==Abstract==

This IIP describes policies for transaction relay to improve privacy and reduce network fingerprinting. It is adapted from BIP 431 concepts for INTcoin.

==Motivation==

Transaction relay timing and topology can leak information about transaction origins. Restrictions on relay behavior improve privacy:
* Prevent timing-based transaction source identification
* Reduce effectiveness of spy nodes
* Improve network partition resistance

==Specification==

===Inbound Connection Limits===

Nodes SHOULD limit transaction relay from inbound connections:
* Apply random delays before relaying received transactions
* Rate-limit inv messages per peer

===Outbound Connection Preferences===

For transaction relay, prefer:
* Block-relay-only connections (2 recommended)
* Full-relay outbound connections (8 recommended)
* Avoid heavy reliance on inbound peers

===Transaction Origin Privacy===

# Add random delay (0-5 seconds) before first announcement
# Announce to outbound peers before inbound peers
# Use different announcement timing per peer

===Dandelion-like Behavior===

Optionally, nodes MAY implement stem-and-fluff:
* Stem phase: Relay to single random peer
* Fluff phase: Normal flooding after random hops

